  "text": "While each product featured is independently selected by our editors, we may include paid promotion. If you buy something through our links, we may earn commission. Read more about our Product Review Guidelines here.If you're building out your wardrobe, there are a few classic staples you should always have on hand — specifically a fitted button-down blouse or work top. There are a plethora of reasons to fill your wardrobe with stylish button-down tops: they're pieces that fit well, make you smile, and can be thrown on in a pinch to create a put-together look. Plus, they can be styled with basically anything in your closet — from comfortable jeans to a sleek pair of white sneakers, or even a sweater vest. A crisp button-down shirt is the one style that's designed to work for it all, regardless of the occasion or dress code.Since it's arguably the most versatile top, we did a little online shopping for you and rounded up the best button-down shirts for women, with styles that come from a range of retailers. Whether you're in the market for a crisp white shirt, something oversize and comfortable, or a linen style that's great as a coverup for the beach, you're bound to find a new favorite piece below. Keep reading to shop our picks.amazon.comBest Affordable Button-Down ShirtAmazon Essentials Classic-Fit Long-Sleeve Button-Down ($17-$24) If you are going somewhere and need to look professional, reach for a structured button-down like this striped style from Amazon. Most are really expensive, which is why we love this affordable option — you truly can't beat an under-$30 price tag, plus it comes in a bunch of colors.target.comBest Long-Sleeved Button-Down ShirtUniversal Thread Long Sleeve Oversized Button-Down Shirt ($25) Come fall, the more long-sleeved tops the better — at least in our closets. We're very excited about the return of colder weather so we can wear more styles like this cozy denim layer. The button-down top would look so cute paired with dark blue jeans for the ultimate denim-on-denim ensemble.ZaraBest Linen Button-Down ShirtZara Oversized Linen Blend Shirt ($45) Everyone needs a great button-down shirt in their arsenal. Pair this linen-blend style from Zara with ripped denim or sleek trousers. Super lightweight, it'll pack easily in a carry-on for any end-of-year travel.AloBest Boyfriend Button-Down ShirtAlo Dreamscape Button-Down Long Sleeve Shirt ($82 originally $118) This boyfriend button-down shirt is the crisp style you'll wear over and over this fall. Button it up to the top or let some buttons go for a more relaxed look. It pairs well with a variety of bottoms.revolve.comBest Cropped Button-Down ShirtSimkhai Renata Cropped Button Down Shirt ($193, originally $275) If you really want to slip into something comfortable, breathable, and easy to move around in, the best way to do that is with a cropped button-down blouse that won't feel too constricting like other more fitted styles. This striped button-down is so flattering and fun. Plus, the cropped design makes it great for teaming with pieces like high-waisted jeans or leggings.shopbop.comBest White Button-Down ShirtFrank \u0026 Eileen Frank Poplin Button Down Shirt ($248) A white button-down shirt should be in everyone's closet. But hey, don't take our word for it — just read through the dozens of rave reviews about this poplin button-down shirt to see why. The piece is supremely comfortable and easy to style. Plus, with a V-neckline and tailored silhouette, it fits like a dream. What's not to love?nordstrom.comBest Silk Button-Down ShirtFrame The Standard Women's Stretch Silk Button-Up Shirt ($398) This silky button-down shirt from Frame requires a bit more of an investment, but it's worth it if you're looking for a piece that's truly designed to last. Crafted from a richly soft silk material, the piece feels cool against skin, yet still maintains a structured shape that looks so sharp while it's on.- Additional reporting by Natasha MarshIndia 